summary: This is an email chain between FBI personnel discussing the service of subpoenas to multiple airlines and Expedia for travel records related to the Maxwell investigation. The emails coordinate deadlines and confirm which subpoenas have been served.

events.title: Subpoena deadline for airlines

events.title: Subpoenas served to airlines
events.description: Subpoenas were served to United, Delta, Southwest, American, and Airline Reporting Corp. Service for Expedia was planned, with information pending from Alaska and JetBlue.

locations: 28 Liberty Street, New York County (Manhattan), New York, New York 10005
keyFacts: The FBI was actively subpoenaing travel records from multiple airlines (United, Delta, Southwest, American, Alaska, JetBlue) and Expedia in relation to the Maxwell investigation as of January-February 2020.
The subpoena to Expedia specifically related to 'Maxwell travel,' indicating a focus on Ghislaine Maxwell's travel patterns.
The deadline for airline responses to these subpoenas was February 7, 2020.
Service for Expedia had to be handled through CT Corp System at a specific New York address.
The document shows coordinated law enforcement effort to obtain travel evidence early in 2020.
